release.notes:
This pressing was plated at [l=Allied Record Company], but pressed by [l=Specialty Records Corporation], as indicated by the Allied "ɑ" logo stamped and "AL-SP" etched in the runouts, and the "E A S T" embossed around the center hole (usually the "T" is the most visible, sometimes the only really visible letter). Remainder of runouts etched.

[r=16115532] is a similar version that was pressed by Allied Record Company. That version does not have the AL-SP etching in the runouts, and will often have the letter "A" embossed in the center of the inner pressing ring on one or both sides.

Front cover hype sticker on shrink wrap: "Features The Hit Single Wild Wild Life"
Front cover hype sticker on shrink wrap: "Includes Songs from the Warner Bros. Motion Picture True Stories"
Back cover sticker on shrink wrap: Tracklist and barcode (0 7599-25512-1). On some copies, the barcode was covered by another plain white sticker.

All basic tracks recorded by Eric "E.T." Thorngren at Sigma Sound, New York and assisted by Melanie West & Nick Del Re.  Additional musicians appearing on A2 recorded by the Omega Audio Remote Facility at the Arcadia Theater, Dallas; additional musicians appearing on A3, B2, B4, and B5 recorded at Studio Southwest, Sunnyvale, Texas.

All songs mixed by Eric "E.T." Thorngren at The Village Recorder Studios, Westwood, California and assisted by Robin Laine, Charles Brocco and Tom Nist, except B4 by Lee Herschberg at Amigo Studios, North Hollywood & B1 by Mick Guzauski at Conway Recording Studios, Hollywood.

Overdubs recorded by Eric "E.T." Thorngren at O'Henry Studios, Toluca Lake, California & assisted by Kathy Botich.

Originally mastered digitally by Jack Skinner at Sterling Sound, New York.

Inner sleeve (cardboard): photos, credits

Catalog number 1-25512 appears on the label.
Catalog number 9 25512-1 appears on the inner sleeve, bottom-right, and jacket spine.
